---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Configuration — OpenCastor Docs"
  description="Understanding the .rcan.yaml configuration file format for OpenCastor robots — RCAN protocol."
  ogUrl="https://opencastor.com/docs/configuration"
>
  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="section-label reveal">Configuration</p>
    <h1 class="reveal reveal-d1">RCAN YAML Format</h1>
    <p class="reveal reveal-d2">Every OpenCastor robot is defined by a single <code style="padding:2px 6px;font-size:0.8125rem">.rcan.yaml</code> config file following the <a href="https://rcan.dev/compatibility" style="color:var(--accent)">RCAN specification</a> (see <a href="https://rcan.dev/compatibility" style="color:var(--accent)">live compatibility matrix</a>).</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section" id="configuration">
    <div class="code-block reveal" style="margin-bottom: 32px">
      <div class="code-header">
        <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
        <span class="code-filename">bob.rcan.yaml — RCAN protocol reference config</span>
      </div>
      <div class="code-body">
<span class="k">rcan_version:</span> <span class="s">"2.2"</span><br><br>
<span class="k">metadata:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">robot_name:</span> <span class="s">"bob"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">robot_uuid:</span> <span class="s">"..."</span> <span class="cm"># auto-generated by castor wizard</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">rrn:</span> <span class="s">"RRN-000000000001"</span> <span class="cm"># assigned at registration (castor register)</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># --- Dual-Brain Block ---</span><br>
<span class="k">brain_reactive:</span> <span class="s">"vla/openvla-7b"</span> <span class="cm"># fast reflexive brain — VLA, SLM, or local model</span><br>
<span class="k">brain_planning:</span> <span class="s">"anthropic/claude-opus-4-6"</span> <span class="cm"># slow planning brain</span><br>
<span class="k">brain_confidence_gate:</span> <span class="n">0.60</span> <span class="cm"># escalate to planner if reactive confidence &lt; gate</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># --- Agent Block ---</span><br>
<span class="k">agent:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">provider:</span> <span class="s">"anthropic"</span> <span class="cm"># anthropic | google | apple | ollama | ...</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">model:</span> <span class="s">"claude-opus-4-6"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">vision_enabled:</span> <span class="v">true</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">safety_stop:</span> <span class="v">true</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># --- Post-Quantum Signing (ML-DSA-65) ---</span><br>
<span class="k">rcan_v22:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">pq_signing_key:</span> <span class="s">"~/.opencastor/pq_signing.key"</span> <span class="cm"># castor keygen --pq</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">pq_public_key:</span> <span class="s">"~/.opencastor/pq_signing.pub"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">require_pq:</span> <span class="v">true</span> <span class="cm"># reject messages without ML-DSA-65 signature</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># --- ISO Conformance (self-declared) ---</span><br>
<span class="k">iso_conformance:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">iso_13482:</span> <span class="v">false</span> <span class="cm"># personal care robots — formal cert not yet obtained</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">iso_10218_2:</span> <span class="v">false</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">iso_42001:</span> <span class="v">true</span> <span class="cm"># AI management system — self-declared</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">eu_ai_act:</span> <span class="v">true</span> <span class="cm"># Art. 12–16 transparency obligations met</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># --- Camera Block ---</span><br>
<span class="k">camera:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">type:</span> <span class="s">"oakd"</span> <span class="cm"># oakd | csi | usb | hailo | auto</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">depth_enabled:</span> <span class="v">true</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">resolution:</span> <span class="s">"640x480"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">fps:</span> <span class="n">30</span><br><br>
<span class="k">physics:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">type:</span> <span class="s">"differential_drive"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">dof:</span> <span class="n">2</span><br><br>
<span class="k">drivers:</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;- <span class="k">protocol:</span> <span class="s">"pca9685_i2c"</span><br>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class="k">address:</span> <span class="s">"0x40"</span><br>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section reveal">
      <h3>Key Blocks</h3>
      <ul style="list-style-type: disc; margin-left: 20px; line-height: 1.8;">
        <li><strong>rcan_version</strong> — Must be <code>"2.2"</code> for new robots. Older <code>"1.x"</code> configs are accepted with a deprecation warning.</li>
        <li><strong>brain_reactive</strong> — Fast reflexive brain (VLA, SLM, or any local model). Handles every request first. Format: <code>"provider/model"</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>brain_planning</strong> — Slow planning brain (Claude, GPT-4.1, Gemini). Activated when reactive confidence drops below <code>brain_confidence_gate</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>brain_confidence_gate</strong> — Float 0–1. Default <code>0.60</code>. Controls when the reactive brain escalates to the planning brain.</li>
        <li><strong>agent</strong> — Primary AI provider and model. Used as planning brain fallback if <code>brain_planning</code> is not set.</li>
        <li><strong>rcan_v22</strong> — Post-quantum signing. <code>pq_signing_key</code> is the ML-DSA-65 keypair generated by <code>castor keygen --pq</code>. Required for v2.2 full conformance.</li>
        <li><strong>iso_conformance</strong> — Self-declared ISO/regulatory flags. Surfaced in <code>castor iso-check</code> and <code>castor conformance</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>camera</strong> — Camera configuration and auto-detect flags.</li>
        <li><strong>physics</strong> — Robot kinematics (differential_drive, ackermann, holonomic, arm).</li>
        <li><strong>drivers</strong> — Hardware drivers (PCA9685, Dynamixel, GPIO, serial, HLabs ACB).</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section reveal" style="margin-top: 32px">
      <h3>Upgrading from RCAN v1.x</h3>
      <p style="margin-bottom:12px">Change <code>rcan_version</code> to <code>"2.2"</code> and add the dual-brain and PQ signing blocks. The runtime accepts v1.x configs with a deprecation warning — no hard break.</p>
      <div class="code-block" style="margin-top:12px">
        <div class="code-header">
          <div class="code-dots"><span></span><span></span><span></span></div>
          <span class="code-filename">migration steps</span>
        </div>
        <div class="code-body">
<span class="cm"># 1. Generate ML-DSA-65 PQ keypair</span><br>
<span class="p">castor keygen --pq</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># 2. Register with Robot Registry Foundation</span><br>
<span class="p">castor register --config my_robot.rcan.yaml</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># 3. Check RCAN protocol conformance (score 0–100)</span><br>
<span class="p">castor conformance --config my_robot.rcan.yaml</span><br><br>
<span class="cm"># 4. Run ISO/EU AI Act self-assessment</span><br>
<span class="p">castor iso-check --config my_robot.rcan.yaml</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="doc-section reveal" style="margin-top: 32px">
